body:
**Description**

I want to fill in a polygon for charting, but it will not fill in.  I was able to fill in a rectangle for comparison.  Below is the sample code.
This is simplified, I actually found this using the shader property of SKPaint. 

**Code**

```
SKImage image = null;
using (var surface = SKSurface.Create(new SKImageInfo(867, 220)))
{ 
	SKCanvas canvas = surface.Canvas;
	canvas.Clear(new SKColor(Color.Transparent.R, Color.Transparent.G, Color.Transparent.B));
	string s = "5,210 5,102.62 289,183.81 838.1,68.57 838.1,210 5,210";
	var points = s.Split(new[] { ' ' }, StringSplitOptions.RemoveEmptyEntries)
		.Select(x => {
			string[] p = x.Split(new[] { ',' }, StringSplitOptions.RemoveEmptyEntries);
			return new SKPoint(Convert.ToSingle(p[0].Trim()), Convert.ToSingle(p[1].Trim()));
		}).ToArray();

	var polygonPaint = new SKPaint()
	{
		Color = SKColors.Red,
		Style = SKPaintStyle.StrokeAndFill,
		IsAntialias = true,
		StrokeJoin = SKStrokeJoin.Round
	};
	SKRect r = new SKRect(50, 50, 100, 100);
	canvas.DrawRect(r, polygonPaint);
	canvas.DrawPoints(SKPointMode.Polygon, points, polygonPaint);
	image = surface.Snapshot();
}
return image;
```

**Expected Behavior**
I would expect the polygon to fill in, it is closed the same way as the rectangle.

**Actual Behavior**
The rectangle is filling in and the polygon is not filling

**Basic Information**
- Version with issue:  2.80.1
- IDE:  Visual Studio 2019
- Platform Target Frameworks: <!-- all that apply, remove the platforms that aren't broken or haven't had any testing -->
  - Windows Classic:  Windows 10

**Screenshots**

